<subSubSection id="1DB1655110306821FF19FEA3E0CB23F3" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="551436DA10306821FF19FEA3E661222F" blockId="8.[136,1452,337,1527]" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FF19FEA3E373220C" bold="true" box="[189,315,1006,1032]" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">Discussion</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D5910306821FEFBFEA2E017220C" authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[351,607,1006,1033]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bhutanensis">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FEFBFEA2E017220C" box="[351,607,1006,1033]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">Saussurea bhutanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FD40FEA2E0B1220D" box="[740,761,1007,1033]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">S.</emphasis>
subgen. 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D5910306821FCFBFEA2E6FD220C" authorityName="Candolle" authorityYear="1838" baseAuthorityName="Cassini" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[863,1205,1007,1033]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Lagurostemon">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FCFBFEA2E199220D" box="[863,977,1007,1033]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">Saussurea</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FBB0FEA2E6FD220C" box="[1044,1205,1007,1032]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">Lagurostemon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on account of its leaf blade being linear, entire, grasslike, and the capitula solitary, 
<quantity id="92539B3F10306821FC91F95CE1D52228" box="[821,925,1041,1068]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" unit="cm" value="1.3" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.0">1–1.6 cm</quantity>
in diameter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="551436DA10306821FF19F978E0CB23F3" blockId="8.[136,1452,337,1527]" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">
<bibRefCitation id="313A4B2B10306821FF19F978E04C224B" author="Grierson, A. J. C. &amp; Springate, L. S." box="[189,516,1077,1103]" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" pagination="1397 - 1632" refId="ref7112" refString="Grierson, A. J. C. &amp; Springate, L. S. (2001) Compositae (Asteraceae). In: Grierson, AJ. C. &amp; Long, D. G. (Eds.) Flora of Bhutan, vol. 2 (3). Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh &amp; Royal Government of Bhutan, pp. 1397 - 1632." type="book chapter" year="2001">Grierson &amp; Springate (2001)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<specimenCount id="43ADFD5310306821FDD6F978E145224B" box="[626,781,1077,1103]" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingCountry id="2DBC764A10306821FCF0F978E1ED224B" box="[852,933,1077,1103]" name="Bhutan" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">Bhutan</collectingCountry>
(
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FC13F978E7EA224B" box="[951,1442,1077,1103]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">F. Ludlow, G. Sherriff &amp; J. H. Hicks 19784</emphasis>
) that is related to 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D5910306821FE9BF915E1C92277" authority="Handel-Mazzetti (1937: 652)" authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityPageNumber="652" authorityYear="1937" box="[319,897,1112,1139]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="columnaris">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FE9BF915E07D2276" box="[319,565,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">Saussurea columnaris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="313A4B2B10306821FD9FF915E1C92277" author="Handel-Mazzetti, H." box="[571,897,1112,1139]" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" pagination="607 - 661" refId="ref7181" refString="Handel-Mazzetti, H. (1937) Neue und bemerkenswerte chinesische Compositen, besonders aus dem Berliner Herbar. Notizblatt des Botanischen Gartens und Museums zu Berlin-Dahlem 13: 607 - 661. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 3994954" type="journal article" year="1937">Handel-Mazzetti (1937: 652)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but they noted this specimen is different from the typical 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D5910306821FF7FF936E33D2291" authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1937" box="[219,373,1147,1173]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="columnaris">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FF7FF936E33D2291" box="[219,373,1147,1173]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">S. columnaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its receptacle naked, achene glandular-stipitate above and habit usually stemless. This kind of specimen was also found from the Tibetean border with 
<collectingCountry id="2DBC764A10306821FD59F9D3E10622BC" box="[765,846,1182,1208]" name="Bhutan" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">Bhutan</collectingCountry>
(
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FCFAF9D2E6DC22BC" box="[862,1172,1182,1208]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">FLPH Tibet Exped.13-2131</emphasis>
) by the present author in 2013. But the present author found its receptacle is not entirely naked but with few short bristles 
<quantity id="92539B3F10306821FB17F98FE74622D8" box="[1203,1294,1218,1244]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 mm</quantity>
long, achenes glabrous, leaves 
<quantity id="92539B3F10306821FEE0F9A9E3E522FB" box="[324,429,1252,1279]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" unit="cm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="1.0">1–2.5 cm</quantity>
long, phyllaries usually narrower and apex acuminate, capitula concealed by dense villous hairs. Typical specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D5910306821FE19F845E01F2326" authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1937" box="[445,599,1288,1314]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="columnaris">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FE19F845E01F2326" box="[445,599,1288,1314]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">S. columnaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Yunnan are different in the receptacle bristles ca. 
<quantity id="92539B3F10306821FB18F845E6B42326" box="[1212,1276,1288,1314]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
long and plants usually stemmed, leaves 
<quantity id="92539B3F10306821FE03F866E3B42342" box="[423,508,1323,1350]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" unit="cm" value="4.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="2.0">2–7 cm</quantity>
long, phyllaries usually broader and apex acute, capitula not concealed by villous hairs. 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D5910306821FF69F802E386236C" authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[205,462,1358,1385]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bhutanensis">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FF69F802E386236C" box="[205,462,1358,1385]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">Saussurea bhutanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D5910306821FD3DF802E6C8236D" authority="Jeffrey &amp; Srivastava (1997: 235)" authorityName="Jeffrey &amp; Srivastava" authorityPageNumber="235" authorityYear="1997" box="[665,1152,1358,1385]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="durgae">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FD3DF802E0EF236D" box="[665,679,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FD11F803E14B236C" box="[693,771,1358,1384]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">durgae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="313A4B2B10306821FCA8F803E6C8236D" author="Jeffrey, C. &amp; Srivastava, R. C." box="[780,1152,1358,1385]" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" pagination="235 - 238" refId="ref7274" refString="Jeffrey, C. &amp; Srivastava, R. C. (1997) A new species of Saussurea DC. (Asteraceae) from eastern Himalaya. Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, India, Section B: Biological Sciences 67 (3 - 4): 235 - 238." type="journal article" year="1997">Jeffrey &amp; Srivastava (1997: 235)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in its caespitose habit and linear grassy leaves, but 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D5910306821FE3EF83FE074238F" authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[410,572,1393,1420]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bhutanensis">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FE3EF83FE074238F" box="[410,572,1393,1420]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">S. bhutanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in its leaves adaxially green, shiny, and glabrous, capitula concealed by villous hairs, and corolla purplish, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D5910306821FDDEF8D8E0AE23AB" authorityName="Jeffrey &amp; Srivastava" authorityYear="1997" box="[634,742,1429,1455]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="durgae">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FDDEF8D8E0AE23AB" box="[634,742,1429,1455]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">S. durgae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in its leaves densely clothed with greyish white wooly hairs on both surfaces, capitula not concealed by villous hairs, and corolla pink. A comparison of 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D5910306821FB47F8F5E7CF23D6" authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[1251,1415,1464,1490]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bhutanensis">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FB47F8F5E7CF23D6" box="[1251,1415,1464,1490]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">S. bhutanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D5910306821FA32F8F5E34E23F2" authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1937" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="columnaris">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FA32F8F5E34E23F2" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">S. columnaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D5910306821FE98F891E3EE23F2" authorityName="Jeffrey &amp; Srivastava" authorityYear="1997" box="[316,422,1500,1526]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="durgae">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FE98F891E30223F2" box="[316,330,1500,1526]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="67DFEAC810306821FEFCF891E3EE23F2" box="[344,422,1500,1526]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="199">durgae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is given in 
<tableCitation id="1829036110306821FD8DF891E0CB23F3" box="[553,643,1500,1527]" captionStart-0="TABLE 5" captionStart-1="TABLE 6" captionStartId-0="8.[136,224,1573,1597]" captionStartId-1="14.[136,224,477,501]" captionText-0="TABLE 5. Comparison of Saussurea bhutanensis, S. columnaris and S. durgae." captionText-1="TABLE 6. Comparison of Saussurea conaensis, S. lhozhagensis and S. nishiokae." pageId="8" pageNumber="199">Table 5.</tableCitation>
</paragraph>
